The passage through the obsidian corridor terminates abruptly at a blank wall.


The surface is perfectly smooth and faintly warm to the touch, and a circular


groove in the stone suggests a door once opened here. Whatever mechanism


operated it has been removed, leaving only the ghost of a threshold and the


tantalising sense that something important lies just beyond.


